President Trump visited the U.S. Treasury Department and praised Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin for his efforts to protect American jobs and finances. Trump discussed the administration's actions to bring back jobs and remove regulations in sectors like energy and auto. He also emphasized the importance of fair trade and getting other countries to pay their fair share for defense and global projects. Trump signed three executive directives, one of which instructs Mnuchin to begin the process of tax simplification. The other two directives focus on reviewing the Dodd-Frank regulations and making the economy more fair and prosperous for all. Trump concluded by mentioning a forthcoming announcement on tax reform.